<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-20T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="756" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/119:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-20T14:00:00-04:00">July
                                        20, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>119. Department’s 108, July 18, 6 p.m. The following from American
                                Consul, Saigon, dated July 19: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“Reference is made to Reed’s telegram July 18, 7 p.m.
                                        relating to ore. French naval authorities at Saigon have
                                        just informed me that they have received instructions from
                                        French Admiralty to release to the Soviet authorities the
                                        wolfram and antimony unloaded from <hi rend="italic">Selenga</hi> upon evidence of purchase by Soviet
                                        Government; Admiralty merely takes the position that cargo
                                        discharged from Soviet ship on advice of contraband
                                        committee could not be object of sales transaction.”</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>